{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"I want to talk to you\nabout the future of medicine."},{"time":4960,"text":"But before I do that, I want to talk\na little bit about the past."},{"time":9080,"text":"Now, throughout much\nof the recent history of medicine,"},{"time":12720,"text":"we've thought about illness and treatment"},{"time":16560,"text":"in terms of a profoundly simple model."},{"time":19960,"text":"In fact, the model is so simple"},{"time":22680,"text":"that you could summarize it in six words:"},{"time":25760,"text":"have disease, take pill, kill something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31080,"text":"Now, the reason\nfor the dominance of this model"},{"time":35840,"text":"is of course the antibiotic revolution."},{"time":38480,"text":"Many of you might not know this,\nbut we happen to be celebrating"},{"time":41680,"text":"the hundredth year of the introduction\nof antibiotics into the United States."},{"time":45760,"text":"But what you do know"},{"time":47400,"text":"is that that introduction\nwas nothing short of transformative."},{"time":52880,"text":"Here you had a chemical,\neither from the natural world"},{"time":56760,"text":"or artificially synthesized\nin the laboratory,"},{"time":59520,"text":"and it would course through your body,"},{"time":62800,"text":"it would find its target,"},{"time":65600,"text":"lock into its target --"},{"time":67280,"text":"a microbe or some part of a microbe --"},{"time":69520,"text":"and then turn off a lock and a key"},{"time":73960,"text":"with exquisite deftness,\nexquisite specificity."},{"time":77520,"text":"And you would end up taking\na previously fatal, lethal disease --"},{"time":81840,"text":"a pneumonia, syphilis, tuberculosis --"},{"time":85000,"text":"and transforming that\ninto a curable, or treatable illness."},{"time":90080,"text":"You have a pneumonia,"},{"time":92480,"text":"you take penicillin,"},{"time":93880,"text":"you kill the microbe"},{"time":95440,"text":"and you cure the disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97600,"text":"So seductive was this idea,"},{"time":100560,"text":"so potent the metaphor of lock and key"},{"time":104760,"text":"and killing something,"},{"time":106320,"text":"that it really swept through biology."},{"time":108360,"text":"It was a transformation like no other."},{"time":112160,"text":"And we've really spent the last 100 years"},{"time":115360,"text":"trying to replicate that model\nover and over again"},{"time":118840,"text":"in noninfectious diseases,"},{"time":120103,"text":"in chronic diseases like diabetes\nand hypertension and heart disease."},{"time":125120,"text":"And it's worked,\nbut it's only worked partly."},{"time":129120,"text":"Let me show you."},{"time":130800,"text":"You know, if you take the entire universe"},{"time":133720,"text":"of all chemical reactions\nin the human body,"},{"time":137240,"text":"every chemical reaction\nthat your body is capable of,"},{"time":140560,"text":"most people think that that number\nis on the order of a million."},{"time":143600,"text":"Let's call it a million."},{"time":144920,"text":"And now you ask the question,"},{"time":146640,"text":"what number or fraction of reactions"},{"time":149320,"text":"can actually be targeted"},{"time":151160,"text":"by the entire pharmacopoeia,\nall of medicinal chemistry?"},{"time":156000,"text":"That number is 250."},{"time":159680,"text":"The rest is chemical darkness."},{"time":162240,"text":"In other words, 0.025 percent\nof all chemical reactions in your body"},{"time":168440,"text":"are actually targetable\nby this lock and key mechanism."},{"time":173680,"text":"You know, if you think\nabout human physiology"},{"time":176760,"text":"as a vast global telephone network"},{"time":180240,"text":"with interacting nodes\nand interacting pieces,"},{"time":184600,"text":"then all of our medicinal chemistry"},{"time":187800,"text":"is operating on one tiny corner"},{"time":190080,"text":"at the edge, the outer edge,\nof that network."},{"time":192800,"text":"It's like all of our\npharmaceutical chemistry"},{"time":196640,"text":"is a pole operator in Wichita, Kansas"},{"time":200440,"text":"who is tinkering with about\n10 or 15 telephone lines."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204880,"text":"So what do we do about this idea?"},{"time":208160,"text":"What if we reorganized this approach?"},{"time":212080,"text":"In fact, it turns out\nthat the natural world"},{"time":215480,"text":"gives us a sense of how one\nmight think about illness"},{"time":220560,"text":"in a radically different way,"},{"time":222240,"text":"rather than disease, medicine, target."},{"time":227080,"text":"In fact, the natural world\nis organized hierarchically upwards,"},{"time":230480,"text":"not downwards, but upwards,"},{"time":232360,"text":"and we begin with a self-regulating,\nsemi-autonomous unit called a cell."},{"time":239640,"text":"These self-regulating,\nsemi-autonomous units"},{"time":242880,"text":"give rise to self-regulating,\nsemi-autonomous units called organs,"},{"time":247720,"text":"and these organs coalesce\nto form things called humans,"},{"time":251920,"text":"and these organisms\nultimately live in environments,"},{"time":255840,"text":"which are partly self-regulating\nand partly semi-autonomous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260920,"text":"What's nice about this scheme,\nthis hierarchical scheme"},{"time":263760,"text":"building upwards rather than downwards,"},{"time":266480,"text":"is that it allows us\nto think about illness as well"},{"time":269880,"text":"in a somewhat different way."},{"time":272400,"text":"Take a disease like cancer."},{"time":276120,"text":"Since the 1950s,"},{"time":277440,"text":"we've tried rather desperately to apply\nthis lock and key model to cancer."},{"time":282991,"text":"We've tried to kill cells"},{"time":285905,"text":"using a variety of chemotherapies \nor targeted therapies,"},{"time":290276,"text":"and as most of us know, that's worked."},{"time":292720,"text":"It's worked for diseases like leukemia."},{"time":294602,"text":"It's worked for some forms\nof breast cancer,"},{"time":297000,"text":"but eventually you run\nto the ceiling of that approach."},{"time":300760,"text":"And it's only in the last 10 years or so"},{"time":303280,"text":"that we've begun to think\nabout using the immune system,"},{"time":306440,"text":"remembering that in fact the cancer cell\ndoesn't grow in a vacuum."},{"time":309560,"text":"It actually grows in a human organism."},{"time":311640,"text":"And could you use the organismal capacity,"},{"time":313960,"text":"the fact that human beings\nhave an immune system, to attack cancer?"},{"time":317127,"text":"In fact, it's led to the some of the most\nspectacular new medicines in cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322480,"text":"And finally there's the level\nof the environment, isn't there?"},{"time":326160,"text":"You know, we don't think of cancer\nas altering the environment."},{"time":329160,"text":"But let me give you an example\nof a profoundly carcinogenic environment."},{"time":334080,"text":"It's called a prison."},{"time":336160,"text":"You take loneliness, you take depression,\nyou take confinement,"},{"time":341320,"text":"and you add to that,"},{"time":343400,"text":"rolled up in a little\nwhite sheet of paper,"},{"time":347000,"text":"one of the most potent neurostimulants\nthat we know, called nicotine,"},{"time":350800,"text":"and you add to that one of the most potent\naddictive substances that you know,"},{"time":355760,"text":"and you have\na pro-carcinogenic environment."},{"time":359520,"text":"But you can have anti-carcinogenic\nenvironments too."},{"time":362000,"text":"There are attempts to create milieus,"},{"time":364720,"text":"change the hormonal milieu\nfor breast cancer, for instance."},{"time":368440,"text":"We're trying to change the metabolic\nmilieu for other forms of cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371880,"text":"Or take another disease, like depression."},{"time":374320,"text":"Again, working upwards,"},{"time":377000,"text":"since the 1960s and 1970s,\nwe've tried, again, desperately"},{"time":381040,"text":"to turn off molecules\nthat operate between nerve cells --"},{"time":385240,"text":"serotonin, dopamine --"},{"time":387440,"text":"and tried to cure depression that way,"},{"time":389280,"text":"and that's worked,\nbut then that reached the limit."},{"time":393000,"text":"And we now know that what you\nreally probably need to do"},{"time":395644,"text":"is to change the physiology\nof the organ, the brain,"},{"time":398640,"text":"rewire it, remodel it,"},{"time":400800,"text":"and that, of course,\nwe know study upon study has shown"},{"time":403400,"text":"that talk therapy does exactly that,"},{"time":405139,"text":"and study upon study\nhas shown that talk therapy"},{"time":407419,"text":"combined with medicines, pills,"},{"time":410560,"text":"really is much more effective\nthan either one alone."},{"time":413840,"text":"Can we imagine a more immersive\nenvironment that will change depression?"},{"time":417440,"text":"Can you lock out the signals\nthat elicit depression?"},{"time":421520,"text":"Again, moving upwards along this\nhierarchical chain of organization."},{"time":427760,"text":"What's really at stake perhaps here"},{"time":430480,"text":"is not the medicine itself but a metaphor."},{"time":433760,"text":"Rather than killing something,"},{"time":435840,"text":"in the case of the great\nchronic degenerative diseases --"},{"time":439560,"text":"kidney failure, diabetes,\nhypertension, osteoarthritis --"},{"time":443080,"text":"maybe what we really need to do is change\nthe metaphor to growing something."},{"time":446676,"text":"And that's the key, perhaps,"},{"time":448640,"text":"to reframing our thinking about medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451160,"text":"Now, this idea of changing,"},{"time":454640,"text":"of creating a perceptual\nshift, as it were,"},{"time":457000,"text":"came home to me to roost in a very\npersonal manner about 10 years ago."},{"time":460320,"text":"About 10 years ago --\nI've been a runner most of my life --"},{"time":463120,"text":"I went for a run, a Saturday morning run,"},{"time":465120,"text":"I came back and woke up\nand I basically couldn't move."},{"time":467800,"text":"My right knee was swollen up,"},{"time":469840,"text":"and you could hear that ominous crunch\nof bone against bone."},{"time":474240,"text":"And one of the perks of being a physician\nis that you get to order your own MRIs."},{"time":479160,"text":"And I had an MRI the next week,\nand it looked like that."},{"time":483160,"text":"Essentially, the meniscus of cartilage\nthat is between bone"},{"time":487480,"text":"had been completely torn\nand the bone itself had been shattered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490920,"text":"Now, if you're looking at me\nand feeling sorry,"},{"time":493400,"text":"let me tell you a few facts."},{"time":495240,"text":"If I was to take an MRI\nof every person in this audience,"},{"time":499440,"text":"60 percent of you would show signs"},{"time":501520,"text":"of bone degeneration\nand cartilage degeneration like this."},{"time":504320,"text":"85 percent of all women by the age of 70"},{"time":508120,"text":"would show moderate to severe\ncartilage degeneration."},{"time":511400,"text":"50 to 60 percent\nof the men in this audience"},{"time":513720,"text":"would also have such signs."},{"time":515080,"text":"So this is a very common disease."},{"time":516880,"text":"Well, the second perk of being a physician"},{"time":519000,"text":"is that you can get\nto experiment on your own ailments."},{"time":522159,"text":"So about 10 years ago we began,"},{"time":524400,"text":"we brought this process\ninto the laboratory,"},{"time":526840,"text":"and we began to do simple experiments,"},{"time":528880,"text":"mechanically trying\nto fix this degeneration."},{"time":531360,"text":"We tried to inject chemicals\ninto the knee spaces of animals"},{"time":536200,"text":"to try to reverse cartilage degeneration,"},{"time":538880,"text":"and to put a short summary\non a very long and painful process,"},{"time":543440,"text":"essentially it came to naught."},{"time":545240,"text":"Nothing happened."},{"time":546880,"text":"And then about seven years ago,\nwe had a research student from Australia."},{"time":551680,"text":"The nice thing about Australians"},{"time":553205,"text":"is that they're habitually used to\nlooking at the world upside down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556546,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557727,"text":"And so Dan suggested to me, \"You know,\nmaybe it isn't a mechanical problem."},{"time":561840,"text":"Maybe it isn't a chemical problem.\nMaybe it's a stem cell problem.\""},{"time":567760,"text":"In other words, he had two hypotheses."},{"time":569680,"text":"Number one, there is such a thing\nas a skeletal stem cell --"},{"time":573520,"text":"a skeletal stem cell that builds up\nthe entire vertebrate skeleton,"},{"time":577064,"text":"bone, cartilage and the fibrous\nelements of skeleton,"},{"time":579620,"text":"just like there's a stem cell in blood,"},{"time":581510,"text":"just like there's a stem cell\nin the nervous system."},{"time":583969,"text":"And two, that maybe that, the degeneration\nor dysfunction of this stem cell"},{"time":587554,"text":"is what's causing osteochondral arthritis,\na very common ailment."},{"time":591080,"text":"So really the question was,\nwere we looking for a pill"},{"time":594320,"text":"when we should have really\nbeen looking for a cell."},{"time":596960,"text":"So we switched our models,"},{"time":599840,"text":"and now we began\nto look for skeletal stem cells."},{"time":603560,"text":"And to cut again a long story short,"},{"time":606080,"text":"about five years ago,\nwe found these cells."},{"time":609800,"text":"They live inside the skeleton."},{"time":612320,"text":"Here's a schematic and then\na real photograph of one of them."},{"time":615240,"text":"The white stuff is bone,"},{"time":617200,"text":"and these red columns that you see\nand the yellow cells"},{"time":620240,"text":"are cells that have arisen\nfrom one single skeletal stem cell --"},{"time":623520,"text":"columns of cartilage, columns of bone\ncoming out of a single cell."},{"time":626840,"text":"These cells are fascinating.\nThey have four properties."},{"time":630160,"text":"Number one is that they live\nwhere they're expected to live."},{"time":633960,"text":"They live just underneath\nthe surface of the bone,"},{"time":636360,"text":"underneath cartilage."},{"time":637920,"text":"You know, in biology,\nit's location, location, location."},{"time":640564,"text":"And they move into the appropriate areas\nand form bone and cartilage."},{"time":644840,"text":"That's one."},{"time":646120,"text":"Here's an interesting property."},{"time":647680,"text":"You can take them out\nof the vertebrate skeleton,"},{"time":650360,"text":"you can culture them\nin petri dishes in the laboratory,"},{"time":652960,"text":"and they are dying to form cartilage."},{"time":654960,"text":"Remember how we couldn't\nform cartilage for love or money?"},{"time":657706,"text":"These cells are dying to form cartilage."},{"time":659650,"text":"They form their own furls\nof cartilage around themselves."},{"time":662680,"text":"They're also, number three,"},{"time":664320,"text":"the most efficient repairers\nof fractures that we've ever encountered."},{"time":668520,"text":"This is a little bone,\na mouse bone that we fractured"},{"time":671840,"text":"and then let it heal by itself."},{"time":673400,"text":"These stem cells have come in\nand repaired, in yellow, the bone,"},{"time":676440,"text":"in white, the cartilage,\nalmost completely."},{"time":679080,"text":"So much so that if you label them\nwith a fluorescent dye"},{"time":682640,"text":"you can see them like some kind\nof peculiar cellular glue"},{"time":686400,"text":"coming into the area of a fracture,"},{"time":688280,"text":"fixing it locally\nand then stopping their work."},{"time":691280,"text":"Now, the fourth one is the most ominous,"},{"time":693640,"text":"and that is that their numbers\ndecline precipitously,"},{"time":697800,"text":"precipitously, tenfold,\nfiftyfold, as you age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702520,"text":"And so what had happened, really,"},{"time":704120,"text":"is that we found ourselves\nin a perceptual shift."},{"time":707000,"text":"We had gone hunting for pills"},{"time":709760,"text":"but we ended up finding theories."},{"time":712280,"text":"And in some ways"},{"time":713520,"text":"we had hooked ourselves\nback onto this idea:"},{"time":716160,"text":"cells, organisms, environments,"},{"time":719080,"text":"because we were now thinking\nabout bone stem cells,"},{"time":721680,"text":"we were thinking about arthritis\nin terms of a cellular disease."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725840,"text":"And then the next question was,\nare there organs?"},{"time":728150,"text":"Can you build this\nas an organ outside the body?"},{"time":730413,"text":"Can you implant cartilage\ninto areas of trauma?"},{"time":734280,"text":"And perhaps most interestingly,"},{"time":736280,"text":"can you ascend right up\nand create environments?"},{"time":738680,"text":"You know, we know\nthat exercise remodels bone,"},{"time":741760,"text":"but come on, none of us\nis going to exercise."},{"time":744200,"text":"So could you imagine ways of passively\nloading and unloading bone"},{"time":749400,"text":"so that you can recreate\nor regenerate degenerating cartilage?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754240,"text":"And perhaps more interesting,\nand more importantly,"},{"time":756645,"text":"the question is, can you apply this model\nmore globally outside medicine?"},{"time":760120,"text":"What's at stake, as I said before,\nis not killing something,"},{"time":764200,"text":"but growing something."},{"time":766280,"text":"And it raises a series of, I think,\nsome of the most interesting questions"},{"time":771120,"text":"about how we think\nabout medicine in the future."},{"time":775040,"text":"Could your medicine\nbe a cell and not a pill?"},{"time":778840,"text":"How would we grow these cells?"},{"time":781240,"text":"What we would we do to stop\nthe malignant growth of these cells?"},{"time":784280,"text":"We heard about the problems\nof unleashing growth."},{"time":788200,"text":"Could we implant\nsuicide genes into these cells"},{"time":791000,"text":"to stop them from growing?"},{"time":793040,"text":"Could your medicine be an organ\nthat's created outside the body"},{"time":797000,"text":"and then implanted into the body?"},{"time":798960,"text":"Could that stop some of the degeneration?"},{"time":801720,"text":"What if the organ needed to have memory?"},{"time":803649,"text":"In cases of diseases of the nervous system\nsome of those organs had memory."},{"time":808440,"text":"How could we implant\nthose memories back in?"},{"time":810920,"text":"Could we store these organs?"},{"time":812760,"text":"Would each organ have to be developed\nfor an individual human being"},{"time":815927,"text":"and put back?"},{"time":818520,"text":"And perhaps most puzzlingly,"},{"time":821160,"text":"could your medicine be an environment?"},{"time":824160,"text":"Could you patent an environment?"},{"time":825840,"text":"You know, in every culture,"},{"time":829320,"text":"shamans have been using\nenvironments as medicines."},{"time":832280,"text":"Could we imagine that for our future?"},{"time":836080,"text":"I've talked a lot about models.\nI began this talk with models."},{"time":839480,"text":"So let me end with some thoughts\nabout model building."},{"time":842200,"text":"That's what we do as scientists."},{"time":844320,"text":"You know, when an architect\nbuilds a model,"},{"time":847640,"text":"he or she is trying to show you\na world in miniature."},{"time":850960,"text":"But when a scientist is building a model,"},{"time":853880,"text":"he or she is trying to show you\nthe world in metaphor."},{"time":857600,"text":"He or she is trying to create\na new way of seeing."},{"time":861480,"text":"The former is a scale shift.\nThe latter is a perceptual shift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866920,"text":"Now, antibiotics created\nsuch a perceptual shift"},{"time":871880,"text":"in our way of thinking about medicine\nthat it really colored, distorted,"},{"time":875720,"text":"very successfully, the way we've thought\nabout medicine for the last hundred years."},{"time":880400,"text":"But we need new models\nto think about medicine in the future."},{"time":884840,"text":"That's what's at stake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":887480,"text":"You know, there's\na popular trope out there"},{"time":890840,"text":"that the reason we haven't had\nthe transformative impact"},{"time":894840,"text":"on the treatment of illness"},{"time":896840,"text":"is because we don't have\npowerful-enough drugs,"},{"time":899720,"text":"and that's partly true."},{"time":902120,"text":"But perhaps the real reason is"},{"time":903640,"text":"that we don't have powerful-enough\nways of thinking about medicines."},{"time":908560,"text":"It's certainly true that"},{"time":911000,"text":"it would be lovely to have new medicines."},{"time":914800,"text":"But perhaps what's really at stake\nare three more intangible M's:"},{"time":919480,"text":"mechanisms, models, metaphors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":923320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":933600,"text":"Chris Anderson:\nI really like this metaphor."},{"time":937040,"text":"How does it link in?"},{"time":938600,"text":"There's a lot of talk in technologyland"},{"time":941760,"text":"about the personalization of medicine,"},{"time":943920,"text":"that we have all this data\nand that medical treatments of the future"},{"time":947360,"text":"will be for you specifically,\nyour genome, your current context."},{"time":951880,"text":"Does that apply to this model\nyou've got here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":955840,"text":"Siddhartha Mukherjee:\nIt's a very interesting question."},{"time":958480,"text":"We've thought about\npersonalization of medicine"},{"time":960720,"text":"very much in terms of genomics."},{"time":962280,"text":"That's because the gene\nis such a dominant metaphor,"},{"time":964880,"text":"again, to use that same word,\nin medicine today,"},{"time":967880,"text":"that we think the genome will drive\nthe personalization of medicine."},{"time":971640,"text":"But of course the genome\nis just the bottom"},{"time":974760,"text":"of a long chain of being, as it were."},{"time":978600,"text":"That chain of being, really the first\norganized unit of that, is the cell."},{"time":982440,"text":"So, if we are really going to deliver\nin medicine in this way,"},{"time":985440,"text":"we have to think of personalizing\ncellular therapies,"},{"time":988280,"text":"and then personalizing\norgan or organismal therapies,"},{"time":991480,"text":"and ultimately personalizing\nimmersion therapies for the environment."},{"time":995320,"text":"So I think at every stage, you know --"},{"time":998440,"text":"there's that metaphor,\nthere's turtles all the way."},{"time":1000880,"text":"Well, in this, there's\npersonalization all the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003285,"text":"CA: So when you say\nmedicine could be a cell"},{"time":1006200,"text":"and not a pill,"},{"time":1008040,"text":"you're talking about\npotentially your own cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1010320,"text":"SM: Absolutely.\nCA: So converted to stem cells,"},{"time":1012720,"text":"perhaps tested against all kinds\nof drugs or something, and prepared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1017280,"text":"SM: And there's no perhaps.\nThis is what we're doing."},{"time":1019840,"text":"This is what's happening,\nand in fact, we're slowly moving,"},{"time":1023600,"text":"not away from genomics,\nbut incorporating genomics"},{"time":1027440,"text":"into what we call multi-order,\nsemi-autonomous, self-regulating systems,"},{"time":1032200,"text":"like cells, like organs,\nlike environments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034829,"text":"CA: Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036227,"text":"SM: Pleasure. Thanks."}]}]}